  <note resp="#BP">A system of cryptography attested in a set of Demotic ostraka from Medinet Madi. The key to this system is simple: the Demotic number must be replaced by the corresponding Greek number in its standard alphabetical notation. Two texts (notices, 2nd cent. A.D.) are published by way of exemplification. - Pp. 241: Appendix. I. List of Greek words encrypted; - 242: Appendix II. List of Greek proper names encrypted.</note>
